## LIGHT MODE RULES

### Surface hierarchy — each layer must be visually distinct

Layer 0 — Page background
  var(--color-base) → #EAF2EF mint cream
  Blobs animate on top of this layer

Layer 1 — Glass panels, sidebar, main panels
  class: glass-panel
  rgba(179,215,255,0.45) icy blue tint plus blur
  border: rgba(37,99,235,0.20)

Layer 2 — Raised surfaces, cards inside panels, inputs
  rgba(255,255,255,0.60) to rgba(255,255,255,0.80)
  Whiter than glass panel to create depth

Layer 3 — Elevated elements, dropdowns, tooltips, popovers
  rgba(255,255,255,0.92) or var(--color-surface-raised)
  Most opaque layer, clearly above everything

### Text contrast — WCAG AA minimum 4.5:1

- Headings: var(--color-text-primary) → #111827
- Body: var(--color-text-secondary) → #374151
- Muted: var(--color-text-muted) → #6B7280
- Accent: var(--color-text-accent) → #1d4ed8

Never in light mode:
- White or near-white text
- rgba(255,255,255,0.X) as text color
- Light gray above #9CA3AF as body text
- Raw #DBFD6B as text color

### Interactive states

Active nav item:
  background rgba(37,99,235,0.12), color #1d4ed8, font-weight 600

Inactive nav hover:
  background rgba(37,99,235,0.07), color #374151

Primary button:
  background #2563EB, color #ffffff
  box-shadow var(--cta-shadow)
  hover bg var(--btn-primary-hover-bg)

Ghost button:
  background var(--color-accent-muted)
  border rgba(37,99,235,0.20)
  color #2563EB
  hover var(--btn-ghost-hover-bg)

### Glassmorphism requirements

- Blobs MUST be present and visible — they provide the blur source
- Every glass surface MUST have semi-transparent background, backdropFilter blur() AND -webkit-backdropFilter blur(), visible border at 0.15–0.25 opacity, box-shadow for depth
- Glass surfaces MUST NOT have background transparent, background opaque color, overflow hidden on parent clipping blur, transform or filter on parent which breaks backdrop-filter

---

## DARK MODE RULES

### Surface hierarchy

Layer 0 — Page background
  var(--color-base) → #181616 carbon black
  Purple/violet blobs at low opacity

Layer 1 — Glass panels
  class: glass-panel
  rgba(24,22,22,0.60) plus blur
  border: rgba(37,99,235,0.22)

Layer 2 — Raised surfaces
  rgba(255,255,255,0.04) to rgba(255,255,255,0.06)
  Slightly lighter than panel

Layer 3 — Elevated elements
  rgba(24,22,22,0.92)
  Most opaque layer

### Text contrast

- Primary: var(--color-text-primary) → #EAF2EF
- Secondary: var(--color-text-secondary) → rgba(234,242,239,0.65)
- Muted: var(--color-text-muted) → rgba(234,242,239,0.40)
- Accent: var(--color-text-accent) → #60a5fa

Never in dark mode:
- Dark text like #111827, #374151, #6B7280 — invisible
- Pure black #000000
- rgba(0,0,0,...) as text color

### Interactive states

Active nav item:
  background rgba(37,99,235,0.12), color #60a5fa, font-weight 600

Inactive nav hover:
  background rgba(37,99,235,0.12), color rgba(234,242,239,0.70)

Primary button:
  background #2563EB same as light
  box-shadow var(--cta-shadow) stronger glow

Stat numbers:
  text-shadow 0 0 12px rgba(37,99,235,0.35)
  Only stat numbers get glow — never body text

### Glassmorphism requirements

- Blobs are purple/violet tinted and must be visible through panels
- Glass border opacity slightly higher than light mode: 0.22 vs 0.20
- Never add white backgrounds — max rgba(255,255,255,0.06) for Layer 2
- Anything more opaque kills glass depth
- Regular body text never gets glow

