## THEME TOGGLE IMPLEMENTATION

- Toggle: set/remove data-theme="dark" on document.documentElement
- Persist: localStorage key "tp-theme"
- Anti-flash: read localStorage in head before first paint
- Icon: Sun for light active, Moon for dark active, both from lucide-react
- After toggling all surfaces must switch — if any surface does not switch it has a hardcoded color, find and fix it

---

## FORBIDDEN PATTERNS — never generate these

- color: #111827                    → use var(--color-text-primary)
- color: #374151                    → use var(--color-text-secondary)
- color: #6B7280                    → use var(--color-text-muted)
- color: #2563eb inline             → use var(--color-accent)
- color: #1d4ed8 inline             → use var(--color-accent-hover)
- background: rgba(37,99,235,...)   → use CSS variable
- background: rgba(179,215,255,...) → use glass-panel class
- background: rgba(24,22,22,...)    → use glass-panel class
- background: white                 → use var(--color-surface-raised)
- background: black                 → use var(--color-base)
- color: white                      → use var(--color-text-primary)
- color: black                      → use var(--color-text-primary)
- prefers-color-scheme              → never, use data-theme only
- [data-theme="dark"] in tsx/ts     → move to globals.css

---

## WHERE HARDCODED VALUES ARE ALLOWED

- globals.css — single source of truth
- lib/constants/planColors.ts — plan color definitions
- lib/constants/subcompetenceTokens.ts — subcompetence tokens
- Nowhere else

